<taxonomicName id="4C634D29863F8674FD356D59FC8FFA9E" box="[740,861,1365,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Apopestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curiosa">
<emphasis id="B917EAB8863F8674FD356D59FC8FFA9E" box="[740,861,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">A. curiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by smaller size, a narrower forewing, the dark brown ground colour of both wings, the almost untraceable cross-lines and the indistinct stigmata. In the male genitalia it differs by the uncus with process, the short tegumen, the plate-like saccus, the asymmetrical ampulla, the bent aedeagus, and the shape of the multiple diverticula of the vesica.
</paragraph>
